# Paddy Husk Machine – Automated Control System (Simulation)

## Overview
This project simulates an **automated heat‑press control system** for molding biodegradable plates from paddy husk.  
The system uses an Arduino, a DS18B20 temperature sensor, a servo motor (press), LEDs, and push buttons.

## How It Works
- Press **START** → Heater LED (red) turns ON.
- Temperature rises (simulated by manually setting DS18B20 to 130°C).
- At 120°C, heater turns OFF, servo rotates to 90° (press), holds for 3 seconds.
- Servo returns to 0°, ready LED (green) turns ON → plate ready.
- **STOP** and **RESET** buttons work at any time.

## Files
- `diagram.json` – Wokwi circuit (connections)
- `code.ino` – Arduino sketch (FSM, temperature reading, servo control)
- `screenshot.png` – Serial Monitor output showing the sequence

## Simulation Tool
[Wokwi](https://wokwi.com) – free online simulator.

## Status
✅ Fully simulated and verified.  


## How to Run
1. Copy `diagram.json` and `code.ino` into a new Wokwi project.
2. Start simulation.
3. Press START, then right‑click DS18B20 → set temperature to 130°C.
4. Watch the servo move and LEDs change.
